	shorttitle = {Factors affecting the learning of foreign language vocabulary},
	doi = {10.1080/14640749308401062},
	abstract = {Investigated the cognitive processes involved in learning foreign language (FL) vocabulary. Results from 47 undergraduates indicate that keyword techniques are effective for receptive learning, but repetition is a superior strategy for learning to produce the foreign word. Performance is optimal when learners combine both strategies. The nature of the keyword is crucial (i.e., imageable noun keywords promote learning, verb keywords actually impede it). A theoretical analysis of the roles of phonological short-term memory, imagery, and lexical factors in FL vocabulary learning is presented. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2018 APA, all rights reserved)},
